premise_source_doc_sentence: Athena  (  -LSB- əˈθiːnə -RSB- Attic Greek : Ἀθηνᾶ , Athēnā , or Ἀθηναία , Athēnaia ; Epic : Ἀθηναίη , Athēnaiē ; Doric : Ἀθάνα , Athānā  )  or Athene  (  -LSB- əˈθiːniː -RSB- Ionic : Ἀθήνη , Athēnē  )  , often given the epithet Pallas  (  -LSB- ˈpæləs -RSB- Παλλὰς  )  , is the goddess of wisdom , craft , and war in ancient Greek religion and mythology .
